### Step 7: Wire Auth Flow

Verify end-to-end:
1. **Signup** (`/[locale]/signup`) → Supabase auth → redirect to `/dashboard`
2. **Login** (`/[locale]/login`) → Supabase auth → redirect to `/dashboard`
3. **Callback** (`/[locale]/callback`) → Supabase session exchange
4. **Middleware** (`middleware.ts`) → Supabase session refresh + protected routes
5. **Dashboard** → fetches real data via API with session token

Check:
- [ ] `apps/web/src/lib/supabase/client.ts` uses correct env vars
- [ ] `apps/web/src/lib/supabase/server.ts` uses correct env vars
- [ ] `apps/web/src/lib/supabase/middleware.ts` refreshes session correctly
- [ ] `middleware.ts` chains i18n + auth correctly
- [ ] Protected routes redirect to `/login` if no session
- [ ] Login page redirects to `/dashboard` if session exists

### Step 8: Error Handling + Loading States

**Toast component:** Create `apps/web/src/components/ui/toast.tsx` (use shadcn/ui toast or simple custom)

**Error boundary pattern:**
```tsx
function ErrorFallback({ error, resetErrorBoundary }: { error: ApiError; resetErrorBoundary: () => void }) {
  const { t } = useTranslation();
  return (
    <div className="flex flex-col items-center gap-4 p-8 text-center" role="alert">
      <AlertCircle className="h-10 w-10 text-destructive" />
      <p className="text-muted-foreground">{t("common.errorGeneric")}</p>
      <button onClick={resetErrorBoundary} className="rounded-lg bg-primary px-4 py-2 text-primary-foreground">
        {t("common.retry")}
      </button>
    </div>
  );
}
```

**Skeleton loaders:** Already exist on dashboard/profile pages. Verify they show during TanStack Query loading state.

